List of Projects Expected To Be Approved At G7 Information Meeting 
The G7 information conference is expected to approve 11 pilot projects
on Sunday to promote international cooperation in using and developing
new technology.
Here is a list: -- Training and education, focusing on language
teaching. -- Global network of electronic libraries. -- Electronic
museums and galleries. -- Developing world data bases on environment
and resource protection. -- Global network to share information on the
risks of natural disasters and emergency management. -- Increased
cooperation in long-distance medicine. -- On-line exchanges between
governments. -- Exchanges of electronic information between small
businesses. -- Maritime information exchange system to improve safety
and environmental protection. -- An inventory of major national and
international projects and studies on the information society and its
social, cultural and economic impact. -- Global inter operability to
build links between the various high-speed networks.
